cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with assigning virtual machines to physical machines, which is a common problem in cloud computing and data centers. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses power consumption, which is a crucial factor in designing efficient network architectures. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimizing power consumption in a system of physical machines. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper aims to minimize power consumption while ensuring that each virtual machine is assigned to exactly one physical machine, which can affect the overall performance of the system. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper studies the hardness and online competitiveness of the Virtual Machine Assignment problem.
